HEADWORD: Southernwood
<hw>South"ern*wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A shrubby species of wormwood (<spn>Artemisia Abrotanum</spn>)
having aromatic foliage. It is sometimes used in making beer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

